cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DC

This paper discusses the state-of-the-art dynamic code analysis platforms for Android and evaluates their effectiveness with samples from known malware corpora as well as known Android bugs like Master Key. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

However, the paper also discusses the properties being analyzed in these platforms, which could fall under the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of these platforms, which could fall under the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages). 

The paper also discusses the potential exploitation of the Master Key bug by malware, which could fall under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the low level of diversity in analysis platforms resulting from code reuse, which could fall under the sub-category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
